        <p>Roof repairs in Grand Rapids typically cost <strong>$300–$2,500</strong> depending on the scope of damage and materials involved. Common repairs include replacing cracked or wind-blown shingles, resealing failed pipe boot flanges, patching deteriorated valley flashing, and fixing chimney step flashing that has pulled away from the masonry. Kamps Professional Roofing is a licensed and insured roofing company based in Grand Rapids, MI, and Daniel Kamps personally assesses every repair before quoting a price.</p>
        <p>Not every roof problem requires a full replacement. A localized leak caused by a single failed pipe boot or a section of shingles torn off during a spring storm is a straightforward fix when caught early. The key is identifying the actual source — water travels along decking and rafters before it shows up as a ceiling stain, so the drip inside your home is rarely directly below the entry point on the roof. With three decades of tracing leaks across Kent County homes, Daniel knows where to look and what patterns to watch for.</p>
        <p>West Michigan's freeze-thaw cycles put particular stress on flashings and sealant joints. Expansion and contraction from temperature swings — Grand Rapids can see 60-degree shifts between January and March — crack rigid caulk and loosen step flashing fasteners over time. Kamps uses flexible sealants rated for Michigan's temperature range and installs flashing with proper kick-out details to prevent recurring failures at wall-to-roof transitions.</p>
        <p>After every repair, you receive a written summary of what was found, what was done, and what to watch going forward. If the repair reveals underlying issues that make replacement a smarter financial decision, Daniel will tell you that honestly — and explain why.</p>
